If the kitchen counter is small or narrow, you can also set it in the sink or pull out the expandable bars to use it over the sink. What a space-saving dish rack in sink!

DURABLE MATERIAL: Sakugi kitchen dish drying rack in sink is made of high-quality stainless steel, which is not easy to rust or deform during use, ensuring the rack is durable enough for long-term use. In addition, the premium silicone leg covers and handle covers can effectively prevent the dish rack from slipping and scratching.

EXPANDABLE BARS: Sakugi expandable dish drying rack measures 13.9"L x 11.9"W x 5.1"H, and the supporting bars is adjustable from 14.4" to 23.1". With a compact size and expandable design, Sakugi dish rack for kitchen counter is an optimal choice for small kitchens. It is important to check the size of the rack is fit your sink BEFORE PURCHASE.

MULTIPURPOSE DESIGN: With a drain rack and a removable cutlery holder, Sakugi large dish drying rack for kitchen counter is capable of holding bowls, plates, mugs, glasses, forks, knives, and other small kitchenware. It's an ideal kitchen necessity for a family of 2-3 people. You can have your various tableware well-organized with Sakugi in sink dish drying rack.

EASY TO MAINTAIN: Sakugi dish drying rack with drainboard features a waterproof and fingerprint-proof black coating. With a simple construction, the dish rack is easy to disassemble to clean. Simply wipe the rack with a damp cloth or rinse it under a running tap if needed. You can effortlessly use and maintain Sakugi dish drainers for kitchen counter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This dish drainer is great
reviews.reviewText: This is really a versatile dish drainer. It can fit in your sink. It has arms so that it can fit over your sink. It has its own draining board with a spout to drain rinse water right into the sink. The only assembly I needed to do was to add the soft covers to the feet of the drain board so that it does not scratch the counter or the sink. It is sturdy and attractive. I am very pleased with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy, versatile, cheap
reviews.reviewText: Very versatile dry rack for kitchen.It can be set directly into the base of the sink itself, including the drain pan (so you do not have to find space to hide the drain pan if you just use it in the sink.)It also has little arms that extend out sideways so it can hover over the base of the sink as well. It is adjustable so it can fit different sized sinks that way.When fully compacted it is small enough to fit in my kitchen sink (which I have an older home with "stock stainless" kitchen sink of average depth).Also, the drain pan will allow you to set it on the counter next to the sink and drain the excess water into the sink at the same time. So if you prefer to dry and leave your sinks empty, it has an option for that too.Overall, makes life easier having a dry rack. Its not extravagant, but its solid and works well for that purpose, easy to fit any way you prefer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for small spaces
reviews.reviewText: This has worked well for my kitchen. I like that I have several options for placing this drying rack, either on the side or hanging over the sink. It holds my chunky square plates and lots of silverware. It holds my breakfast dishes, containers from my lunch, and dinner dishes. I usually have to wash the cookware from dinner separately or dry on a towel but that's a lot of dishes for a space saver rack. Constructed well and does not feel flimsy.The only 2 things I didn't like about this rack tray were the feet and the length of the drain. The rubber covers for the feet don't fit snug so I have to be careful when moving it or they fall off. I wish the drain was a little longer because the shape of the lip of my sink meant I had to keep the tray right on the edge. I would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sink Too Tall...
reviews.reviewText: This product is great! Well designed, sturdy, and holds enough while also not taking up too much space.Unfortunately, which is in no way the products fault, the lip of our sink is TALL. So the spout feature will not work correctly until we find a way to raise the product an inch. This is something to keep in mind when shopping for a dish rack! Learn from my oops!Other than that, it's a great product and looks very nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: There is nothing overly fancy with the product. I took it out of the box and was able to use it immediately without assembly. The product adjusts to fit my sink, well, and is sturdy. I like having the option to place it on the counter with the additional bottom piece, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble, seems sturdy enough to be of use for quite a while. My boyfriend has a tiny house with a tiny sink, so this was perfect. Doesn't take up too much counter space, and the drain works exactly how it should.These aren't complaints, just something to mention. It definitely looks smaller in person, and if you're trying to dry multiple pots and pans...good luck. Even getting one in there is a challenge. But I still think it's totally worth the money--heck, it was an early Christmas gift and he LOVES it. (This man is excited when I buy him toilet paper, he's not difficult to please thankfully.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Smaller then thought!
reviews.reviewText: Love the concept of these because you don’t have those nasty mats and it drains in the sink. But I don’t like how close it has to be to the sink to reach!! Could make the drain spout longer. Also wish the cutlery holder would be on the outside cause it takes a lot of room in an already smaller drain board! Good for single person or someone who doesn’t have a lot of dishes at one time

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Keeps drying dishes off counter
reviews.reviewText: As described, black with coated handle to cushion against counters. Works best, but not exclusively, with an undermount sink that has faucet installed with single hole directly into counter. It's workable with a sink with a faucet that has a metal plate mount, but the extended support bars will either rest on faceplate, making it uneven--or if not, it will not have as much room to perch (this is the option I choose, and I'm careful). Wish I had this years ago! It holds my cutting boards vertically, it holds my largest pots and bowls. It would not hold those AND dishes, it's more for a person with either a dishwasher or household of 1 or 2 without dishwasher, in my opinion.

reviews.reviewerName: Excelente artículo, quedó perfecto en el entrepaño abajo de la tarja. De buena calidad .
reviews.reviewText: Escurridor de mala calidad, los materiales feos. El empaque llegó abierto y le faltaba el compartimento para los cubiertos.
